&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;111 Service Advisor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exeter&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OPS-0265&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Devon Doctors Group is currently recruiting for Service Advisors to work within our Integrated Urgent Care Services at our offices based in Exeter. We are currently recruiting for various hours per week which includes 2 weekends a month.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the position:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS 111 is a fundamental part of the Devon Integrated Urgent Care Service (IUCS) which is a non-emergency telephone service providing patient’s advice to the most appropriate urgent care service they require. As a Service Advisor, you will be answering inbound calls and supporting members of the public in need of medical advice by directing them to the most appropriate urgent care, primarily for dental support. You will be responsible to ensure that all calls are answered promptly, accurately and professionally in line with the performance standards. Depending on your rota pattern, there is scope to answer a significant range of calls, offering a diverse and varied opportunity to make a positive difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates for this position must;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have local geographical knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in customer facing environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent telephone manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent keyboard skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a positive attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have the ability to record information accurately and correctly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll receive in return:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£8.82 per hour + enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;22 days holiday (plus bank holidays) pro rata&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle to work scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 Paid volunteering day per year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perkbox&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Devon Doctors?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Devon Doctors Group has been delivering urgent primary care in Devon to an exceptional standard for twenty two years. Our sister companies, Access Health and Access Dental also offer a range of dentistry and primary care services across the Peninsula.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to being an inclusive employer with a diverse workforce. We encourage applications from people from all backgrounds, cultures and experiences to contribute to the diversity of our organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To find out more about this position please contact the recruitment team on 01392 823156 or ddooh.clinicalworkforce@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
